[[File:Gospels russia.jpg|thumb|Mstislav Gospel]] '''Mstislav Gospel''' is a 12th-century manuscript of the four [[Gospel]]s on parchment in [[Old Church Slavonic]].
== Description == The manuscript contains the text of the four Gospels on 213 parchment leaves (35.3 by 28.6&nbsp;cm). The manuscript was prepared on the order of [[Mstislav I of Kiev]]. Currently it is housed in the [[State Historical Museum]] in [[Moscow]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.manuscripts.ru/gospel/SK_51.html | title = Евангелие апракос полный ("Мстиславово евангелие") | publisher = Славянские Евангелия. Интернет-версия электронного многотекстового издания | accessdate = 2013-10-14 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url = http://www.nlr.ru/eng/exib/Gospel/drus/52.html | title = Copy of Mstislav Gospel. 1855. Copyist: Osip Bodyansky | publisher = The National Library of Russia | work = | year = 2007 | accessdate = 2013-10-14}}</ref>
